entries.meaning: The process of frogmarching a person.

verbs.description: frogmarch (third-person singular simple present frogmarches, present participle frogmarching, simple past and past participle frogmarched)

entries.meaning: To march or force a person forward while holding their arms from behind or the side, as a prisoner.
(figurative) To force a person forward against their will.
examples: The wind frogmarched me at a run into the house.

entries.meaning: (formerly) To carry a person face-down with one person holding each limb.
To forcibly relocate a person, especially in a degrading or humiliating manner.
